 that place for the longest time. Ditto the <strong>Lazard</strong> brother=
s, who founded and controlled the firm before their
cousins, the <strong>David-Weill</strong> family, took control.=C2=A0<br/><=
br/>This sort of intentional nepotism only became unfashionable after the b=
ig Wall Street firms started going public=E2=80=94beginning in 1970 with Do=
naldson, Lufkin &amp; Jenrette=E2=80=94adding outside investors and shareho=
