;Inter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0=
px;line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">One thing I=E2=80=99ve always admired abou=
t Andrew is how modest he is
for a guy with such a prominent position in the world of financial news. He=
 discussed the process of researching and writing <em>1929</em> with that s=
ame kind of humility. He told me that the process was like assembling piece=
s of an elaborate jigsaw puzzle, any one of which might send him down =E2=
=80=9Cthese weird rabbit holes.=E2=80=9D He=E2=80=99d go to the library at =
Harvard and just sit in front of a pile of documents: =E2=80=9CI was like, =
=E2=80=98Oh, there=E2=80=99s all this stuff that I never read before. This =
is pretty cool. I can=E2=80=99t
believe that there=E2=80=99s a transcript of this phone call with the presi=
dent.=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">He hoped to get a lot of=
 work done during the pandemic, but it turned out to be more difficult than=
 he thought. As a visiting non-student, he was barred from entering many co=
llege libraries. Instead, he paid graduate students, who were in the stacks=
 working on their dissertations, to hunt down documents=E2=80=94a veritable=
 =E2=80=9Cblack
market,=E2=80=9D he joked. =E2=80=9CI used to pay people by the hour to tak=
e pictures with their iPhones,=E2=80=9D he said, =E2=80=9Cto document hundr=
eds and hundreds of pages. I created these crazy Dropbox folders, where the=
y would upload the documents to me.=E2=80=9D Every upload got the writer=E2=
=80=99s attention: =E2=80=9CThese crazy scans would come in, someone would =
send me 100 pages and I would stop everything. I=E2=80=99d miss dinner for =
no reason. I=E2=80=99d work on the book on the weekend, when maybe I should=
 be doing something better with the family.=E2=80=9D
After the pandemic, he returned to the libraries to get the documents himse=
lf.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;">Eventually, the puzzle came together via a few crucial pieces toward =
the end of the process that unlocked the larger, 400-page narrative. =E2=80=
=9CThere are certain characters in the book who have been well reported on =
over the years,=E2=80=9D he said, =E2=80=9Cbut they=E2=80=99ve sort of been=
 reported on in a siloed way. You would read a biography of somebody, but y=
ou wouldn=E2=80=99t
necessarily have them in the same room with=E2=80=94or even know that they =
were <em>related</em> to=E2=80=94some other person. But then if you really =
dig into that person, you discover that they were. That actually was a lot =
of fun.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
